		<div id="welcome">

			<h4>*ABOUT STAGE 1</h4>
			Each or any of the <i>Terms, Concept or Specific Objects</i> [words] presented in Stage 1 may invoke personal feelings, spark a particular philosophical interest, connect with you on spiritual level, all three or none at all. Based on your understanding of the words, it’s up to you to reflect on your life’s experience and make selections using our custom graphic interface. (Don't feel you have to select every category for every word)<a style="font-weight:700;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="UI Example"> See Example</a>
			<br /><br />
			<img src="img/s1Img.jpg" style="float:left; margin:0 20px 15px 0;"/>
			<div>
				<strong>Select up to four categories for any given word</strong><br />
				<ul class="about">
					<li>Man's View of Himself (Himself/Herself)</li>
					<li>Man's Connections with Other than Himself</li>
					<li>Man's View of the World</li>
					<li>Man's Physical Activities</li>
				</ul>
				<strong>The word "Man" means the <i>universal man</i> of which you are an example. <br />As such, you may consider:</strong><br />
            	<ul class="about">
					<li><a style="font-weight:700;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="Personalize">Personalizing some or all words to yourself</a></li>
					<li><a style="font-weight:700;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="Others Exclusively">Thinking of others exclusively</a></li>
					<li><a style="font-weight:700;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="Yourself and Others">Thinking of yourself and others together</a></li>
            	</ul>
			<strong><a style="font-weight:700;color:black;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="Opinion">Opinion</a></strong>
			<ul class="about">
        <li><a style="font-weight:700;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="Foundation">Foundation</a> -- Existence | Essence | Substance | Accident</li>
				<li><a style="font-weight:700;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="Spiritual">Spiritual</a> -- Not composed of parts | will not deteriorate</li>
				<li><a style="font-weight:700;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="Material">Material</a> -- Composed of parts | can deteriorate</li>
				<li><a style="font-weight:700;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="Material Spiritual Converging">Material & Spiritual Converging</a> -- unify in a way where, together, it's more than when seperate.</li>
				<!--Hypothetical 4: You eat <strong>bread</strong> all the time but never gave it much thought. One day you read how the invention of <strong>bread</strong> was quintessential in man's ability to thrive today.-->
			</ul>
			
			</div><br />
			
			<div id="howto-msg">Like anything else, using Ybigh will make you better at using Ybigh. While it may feel awkward at first, you'll get the hang of it. Continue on to<a href="https://ybigh.herokuapp.com/n-stage1"> Stage 1</a></div>
		 	
